43 So I stopped to make out his features;
44 and the gentle guide stopped with me,
45 and consented that I should go back a little.

52 And he to me: “I tell it unwillingly;
53 but your clear speech compels me,
54 which makes me remember the ancient world.

58 And not only do I, a Bolognese, weep here;
59 rather, this place is so full of them,
60 that so many tongues are not now learned

61 to say ‘sipa’ between the Savena and the Reno;
62 and if you want proof or testimony of this,
63 call to mind our avaricious nature”.

67 I rejoined my escort;
68 then with a few steps we came
69 to where a crag jutted out from the bank.

70 We climbed it quite easily;
71 and, turning to the right along its ridge,
72 we departed from those eternal circles.

